      "content": "thanks for the overview. i've been talking to some other parents at the bake sale and they seem really worried that the school is basically pushing a specific agenda and ignoring what families actually believe. on the other hand, some people are saying the school is just doing its job to make kids feel safe. \n\ndoes it feel like one side is more based on actual facts/science while the other is just based on tradition or something? like, is there a way to tell which viewpoint is more 'correct' in this situation?",
